{"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/StateManagement","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/ThemingGuide","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/FocusSystem","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/StatusBarGuide","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/AppearanceAndColors","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/CustomViews","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/KeyboardShortcuts","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/PaletteReference","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/ListAndTable","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/LayoutSystem"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Guides","title":"Guides"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Preferences"},"abstract":[{"text":"Pass data from child views up to their ancestors.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/tuikit\/preferences"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TUIkit’s preference system enables "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"bottom-up data flow"}]},{"type":"text","text":": the reverse of environment values. While the environment passes data down from parent to child, preferences let child views publish values that ancestors can observe and react to."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The system mirrors SwiftUI’s preference API and consists of three parts:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PreferenceKey"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Protocol that defines a named value type with a default and a reduce strategy","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"PreferenceValues","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Type-safe storage that holds all preference values for a scope"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PreferenceStorage"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Stack-based collector that manages preference contexts per render pass"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A built-in example is ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/NavigationTitleKey","isActive":true},{"text":": a child view sets ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".navigationTitle(\"Settings\")"},{"text":", and the enclosing navigation container reads that preference to render the title bar.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Defining-a-Preference-Key","text":"Defining a Preference Key","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A preference key declares what type of value it carries and how multiple values from sibling children are combined:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct CounterKey: PreferenceKey {","    static let defaultValue: Int = 0","","    static func reduce(value: inout Int, nextValue: () -> Int) {","        value += nextValue()","    }","}"]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"defaultValue","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Returned when no child has set this preference"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reduce(value:nextValue:)"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Combines values when multiple children set the same key"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reduce"},{"type":"text","text":" implementation simply takes the last value. Override it when you need additive behavior (summing counts), array collection, or other merge strategies."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Setting-a-Preference","text":"Setting a Preference","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Child views publish a preference using the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".preference(key:value:)"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct ItemView: View {","    var body: some View {","        Text(\"Item\")","            .preference(key: CounterKey.self, value: 1)","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Under the hood, this wraps the view in a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PreferenceModifier"},{"type":"text","text":" that calls "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"preferences.setValue(_:forKey:)"},{"type":"text","text":" during rendering. The value is reduced into the current scope using the key’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reduce"},{"type":"text","text":" function."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Observing-Preferences","text":"Observing Preferences","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Ancestor views react to collected preferences using ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".onPreferenceChange(_:perform:)"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct ItemList: View {","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            ItemView()","            ItemView()","            ItemView()","        }","        .onPreferenceChange(CounterKey.self) { totalCount in","            \/\/ totalCount == 3 (three children each set value: 1, additive reduce)","        }","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The modifier pushes a new preference context, renders all children (which set their preferences), pops the context, and fires the callback with the accumulated result.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"The-Navigation-Title-Shortcut","text":"The Navigation Title Shortcut","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TUIkit provides "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/NavigationTitleKey"},{"type":"text","text":" as a built-in preference key with a convenience modifier:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct SettingsPage: View {","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            Text(\"App settings go here\")","        }","        .navigationTitle(\"Settings\")","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"NavigationTitleKey","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" uses the default ","type":"text"},{"code":"reduce","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (last value wins), so the deepest child’s title takes precedence.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"How-Preferences-Flow-per-Frame","text":"How Preferences Flow per Frame","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Preferences are collected fresh every frame. Here’s the lifecycle within a single render pass:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Reset"}]},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RenderLoop.render()"},{"type":"text","text":" calls "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"preferences.beginRenderPass()"},{"type":"text","text":", clearing all callbacks and resetting the stack to a single empty context"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Set"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": As the view tree renders top-down, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PreferenceModifier"},{"type":"text","text":" views call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"setValue(_:forKey:)"},{"type":"text","text":", which reduces values into the current stack frame"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Scope"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OnPreferenceChangeModifier"},{"text":" pushes a new context before rendering its subtree, isolating child preferences","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Collect"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": After the subtree finishes, the modifier pops the context (merging into the parent) and fires the callback with the scoped result","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Discard"}]},{"type":"text","text":": At the start of the next frame, everything resets: stale preferences never persist"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This per-frame reset ensures preferences always reflect the current view tree. Removed views stop contributing automatically."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Reduce-Strategies","text":"Reduce Strategies","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reduce"},{"type":"text","text":" function determines how multiple children’s values combine. Common patterns:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"header":"row","type":"table","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Strategy"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use Case"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Last value wins"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value = nextValue()"},{"type":"text","text":" (default)"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Titles, labels: deepest child wins"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Additive"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"value += nextValue()","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Counting items, summing heights","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Array collection","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"value.append(contentsOf: nextValue())","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Gathering menu items, breadcrumbs"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Array collection example","struct BreadcrumbKey: PreferenceKey {","    static let defaultValue: [String] = []","","    static func reduce(value: inout [String], nextValue: () -> [String]) {","        value.append(contentsOf: nextValue())","    }","}"]}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit"]]},"metadata":{"role":"collectionGroup","modules":[{"name":"TUIkit"}],"title":"Preferences"},"references":{"doc://TUIkit/documentation/TUIkit/StatusBarGuide":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Configure the shortcut bar at the bottom of the terminal.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/tuikit\/statusbarguide","kind":"article","role":"article","title":"Status Bar","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/StatusBarGuide"},"doc://TUIkit/documentation/TUIkit/AppearanceAndColors":{"url":"\/documentation\/tuikit\/appearanceandcolors","title":"Appearance and Colors","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/AppearanceAndColors","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Control border styles, visual appearances, and the color system."}],"kind":"article","role":"article"},"doc://TUIkit/documentation/TUIkit/NavigationTitleKey":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/NavigationTitleKey","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"NavigationTitleKey","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"A preference key for the navigation title.","type":"text"}],"title":"NavigationTitleKey","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/tuikit\/navigationtitlekey","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"tex